        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1>Kacper Werema</h1>
        <p class="lede mt-sm">Head of Engineering at Oaasis. Took a €4.9M-funded startup from 0 to 1 — leading a team of eight (and growing) to build the go-to supply chain planning platform for €30–60M consumer goods companies, now expanding into enterprise.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose">

        <h2>Currently</h2>
        <p>
          As Head of Engineering at <strong>Oaasis</strong> — a €4.9M-funded startup — I've taken the company
          from 0 to 1: building the engineering team, the technical foundations, and the product itself
          in one of the hardest domains there is, supply chain planning. I lead a team of eight, own the
          engineering department end to end, and keep delivery fast, the team motivated, and every release
          tied to real business value.
        </p>
        <p>
          We've made the product the go-to supply chain planning solution for €30–60M-revenue consumer
          goods companies, and we're now winning enterprise clients far larger — including accounts with
          €80M and €200M in revenue. I keep us on the frontier of AI tooling in our day-to-day workflow,
          and I stay hands-on across the full stack — a NestJS API, a React design system, and Rust services
          for optimization, forecasting, and data ingestion — as the platform's most prolific contributor
          with over <strong>1,300 commits</strong>.
        </p>

        <h2>What I've built</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Took Oaasis from 0 to 1 — building the engineering team, technical foundations, and product as Head of Engineering at a €4.9M-funded startup.</li>
          <li>Built the go-to supply chain planning solution for the core segment: consumer goods companies in the €30–60M revenue range.</li>
          <li>Expanded upmarket with enterprise wins well beyond the core segment, landing clients with revenues up to €200M.</li>
          <li>Shipped a production-grade product in a genuinely complex domain — supply chain optimization, forecasting, inventory, and constrained allocation.</li>
          <li>Lead and set direction for a team of eight, driving high delivery, an AI-first workflow, team morale, and business value.</li>
          <li>Hands-on across the full TypeScript + Rust stack as the codebase's top contributor (1,300+ commits).</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Track record</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Santander Nordic</strong> — Designed quality processes that cut release cycles from 4 months to 6 weeks; built test-automation foundations across 6 teams (28 engineers).</li>
          <li><strong>Swoop Funding</strong> — Scaled the platform from 0 to 50k+ businesses, led the monolith → microservices and multi-tenant migration that secured a £5M grant.</li>
          <li><strong>Staff Bit</strong> — Co-founded and led as CTO to a successful exit; ran enterprise transformations for clients including Santander and Zara.</li>
          <li><strong>Euvic</strong> — Built architecture serving 2M daily users at 99.9% availability and opened a new subsidiary.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How I think</h2>
        <p>
          I'm a systems thinker who's relentlessly business-value-oriented. Technical complexity isn't a
          selling point — ROI, leverage and reliability are. I favour right-sized solutions over both
          over-engineering and fragility, and I believe quality is a team effort, not a gate at the end.
        </p>
        <p>
          I created <strong>P.I.R.A.T.E.S.</strong>, a framework for evaluating and advancing quality
          maturity in engineering organisations, and I facilitate CTO mastermind sessions — because the
          top is lonely, and the right peer conversation changes decisions.
        </p>

        <h2>Stack</h2>
        <p>
          TypeScript / NestJS, React, Rust, C#/.NET, Python, Azure, AWS — and AI agents and automation
          wherever they create real leverage.
        </p>

        <h2>Beyond work</h2>
        <p>
          Based in Poland, married with two small kids — family comes first. Outside of that: golf,
          board games, Dungeons &amp; Dragons, and writing about engineering, leadership and living
          deliberately on <a href="https://kacperwerema.substack.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">my newsletter</a>.
        </p>

